item.title: C
item.description: My mother used to take a can of ready-to-bake biscuit dough, form the dough into rings and deep fry it in a big red pot. Then she’d drain them on a paper towel and sprinkle them with table sugar. ⊕ it was pretty good but you’d feel sick halfway through eating just one!
